20 SECTION 2. ORS 609.420 is amended to read:
21 609.420. (1) Whenever an authorized representative of [an enforcing agency] the State Depart-
22 ment of Agriculture is advised or has reason to believe that an animal rescue entity is operating
23 without a license, the authorized representative may visit and conduct an on-site investigation of the
24 premises of the animal rescue entity. The purpose of an investigation under this section is to de-
25 termine whether the animal rescue entity is subject to the requirements of ORS 609.415.
26 (2) At any reasonable time, an authorized representative of [an enforcing agency] the depart-
27 ment, a law enforcement agency or the United States Department of Agriculture may conduct an
28 on-site investigation of the premises of any licensed animal rescue entity to determine whether the
29 entity is in compliance with ORS 609.415 or a rule adopted thereunder.
30 (3) An authorized representative of the [enforcing agency] State Department of Agriculture
31 or a law enforcement agency shall conduct an on-site investigation of the premises of any licensed
32 animal rescue entity if the department or agency receives a complaint about the animal rescue
33 entity related to the failure to comply with the requirements of ORS 609.415 or a rule adopted
34 thereunder that the department or agency determines is credible and serious. The investigation
35 by the department or agency shall be limited to determining if the animal rescue entity has failed
36 to comply with the requirements of ORS 609.415 or a rule adopted thereunder.
37 (4) Any state agency that receives a complaint about a licensed animal rescue entity shall notify
38 the [enforcing agency] department about the complaint and any subsequent action taken by the
39 state agency based on that complaint.
40 [(5) A licensed animal rescue entity shall permit an authorized representative of the enforcing
41 agency to inspect records of the animal rescue entity and shall furnish any reports and information
